&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;216&quot; data-end=&quot;234&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;216&quot; data-end=&quot;234&quot;&gt;About LumiMeds&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;251&quot; data-end=&quot;466&quot;&gt;LumiMeds is a fast-growing U.S.-based telehealth startup focused on weight management and long-term metabolic health. We are building the next generation of e-commerce and clinical infrastructure from the ground up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;468&quot; data-end=&quot;684&quot;&gt;As an early-stage company, we move quickly, operate with limited layers, and expect high ownership from every team member. There is no bureaucracy here — decisions happen fast, priorities evolve, and builders thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;686&quot; data-end=&quot;834&quot;&gt;We are a remote-first, globally distributed team that values clarity, accountability, and people who take initiative rather than wait for direction.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About LumiMeds&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LumiMeds is a telehealth platform making GLP-1, hormone, and longevity therapies accessible to everyday people. We&#39;re growing fast and looking to build a high-performing affiliate program that puts us in front of the right audiences through trusted voices and partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an affiliate marketing operator who can build and run our affiliate program from the ground up — or take a scrappy early program and scale it into a meaningful acquisition channel. You know the ecosystem: the networks, the publishers, the influencers, the deal structures, and how to keep partners activated and performing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on role. You&#39;ll own the channel end to end — recruiting partners, negotiating terms, managing payouts, and optimizing for cost-per-patient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage LumiMeds&#39; affiliate and partner program across networks (Impact, ShareASale, CJ, or similar) and direct relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruit and onboard high-fit affiliates — health bloggers, wellness creators, comparison sites, coupon platforms, email publishers, and telehealth review sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate commission structures, CPA deals, and hybrid arrangements that align partner incentives with patient LTV&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Activate and re-engage existing partners — create promotions, provide creative assets, and run performance reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor fraud, compliance, and brand safety across all affiliate placements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with legal/compliance to ensure all affiliate messaging meets FDA/FTC guidelines for health and compounded medication claims&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report on affiliate contribution: new patients, revenue, CAC, ROAS, and LTV by partner segment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and test adjacent partnership models — referral programs, loyalty integrations, co-marketing deals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years managing affiliate or performance partnership programs — brand side or agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct experience with at least one major affiliate network (Impact, ShareASale, CJ, Rakuten, or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of CPA, CPL, and hybrid commission structures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience recruiting and managing publisher and creator relationships at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with fraud detection, compliance monitoring, and brand safety in affiliate channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data-driven — comfortable pulling reports, building dashboards, and making optimization decisions from performance data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: experience in telehealth, DTC health, wellness, or subscription businesses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: existing relationships with health/wellness publish

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;216&quot; data-end=&quot;234&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;216&quot; data-end=&quot;234&quot;&gt;About LumiMeds&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;251&quot; data-end=&quot;466&quot;&gt;LumiMeds is a fast-growing U.S.-based telehealth startup focused on weight management and long-term metabolic health. We are building the next generation of e-commerce and clinical infrastructure from the ground up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;468&quot; data-end=&quot;684&quot;&gt;As an early-stage company, we move quickly, operate with limited layers, and expect high ownership from every team member. There is no bureaucracy here — decisions happen fast, priorities evolve, and builders thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;686&quot; data-end=&quot;834&quot;&gt;We are a remote-first, globally distributed team that values clarity, accountability, and people who take initiative rather than wait for direction.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Remote (Europe, South America)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Full-Time Contract&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a creative and detail-oriented Graphic Designer to support our marketing, growth, and brand initiatives. This role works closely with our Marketing and Creative teams to produce high-quality visuals across digital platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you understand brand consistency, work fast without sacrificing quality, and can take direction while adding creative input — you&#39;ll thrive here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Design visual assets for social media, ads, email, web, and landing pages&lt;br&gt;- Create graphics for marketing campaigns, product launches, and promotions&lt;br&gt;- Maintain brand consistency across all design outputs&lt;br&gt;- Collaborate with marketing, content, and growth teams on creative concepts&lt;br&gt;- Revise designs based on feedback and performance insights&lt;br&gt;- Manage multiple design requests and deadlines in a fast-paced environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- 4+ years of experience in graphic design or a similar role&lt;br&gt;- Strong portfolio demonstrating digital-first design work&lt;br&gt;- Proficiency in design tools (Adobe Creative Suite, Figma, Canva, or similar)&lt;br&gt;- Understanding of branding, layout, typography, and color&lt;br&gt;- Ability to take feedback well and iterate quickly&lt;br&gt;- Strong English communication skills&lt;br&gt;- Experience in healthcare, wellness, SaaS, or startup environments is a plus&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Experience designing for paid ads (Meta, Google, TikTok)&lt;br&gt;- Basic understanding of marketing funnels or conversion-focused design&lt;br&gt;- Motion graphics or short-form video design experience&lt;br&gt;- Familiarity with AI image tools (Midjourney, Adobe Firefly, or similar)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Why LumiMeds?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Remote-first, globally distributed team&lt;br&gt;- Clear creative direction and brand standards&lt;br&gt;- Fast turnaround, low bureaucracy&lt;br&gt;- Opportunity to grow with a scaling healthtech company&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;726&quot; data-end=&quot;742&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;726&quot; data-end=&quot;742&quot;&gt;How to Apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;744&quot; data-end=&quot;911&quot;&gt;If this role sounds like a fit, we’d love to hear from you. Please submit your application in English and ensure your resume reflects relevant experience for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;913&quot; data-end=&quot;1074&quot;&gt;This position is open to candidates based in approved locations, depending on the role and business

